      <item>
        <title>5 Git tips for intermediate users</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;5 tips to show (once again) that Git is amazing:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Fetch a file from another branch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# without changing your current branch&lt;/span&gt;
git checkout other_branch -- path/to/file 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# See what branches are merged&lt;/span&gt;
git checkout master 
git branch --merged
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Use --no-merged to see the branches&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# not yet merged&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Have Git auto-correct you&lt;/span&gt;
git config --global help.autocorrect 1
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Example:&lt;/span&gt;
git commti 
WARNING: You called a Git &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;command &lt;/span&gt;named &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;commti&#39;&lt;/span&gt;, which does not exist. 
Continuing under the assumption that you meant &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;commit&#39;&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Show word changes in diff&lt;/span&gt;
git diff --word-diff 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# Set remote branch tracking by default&lt;/span&gt;
git config --global push.default tracking&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

</description>
