      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Productivity boost with shell aliases</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Using aliases to give commands useful options by default is a good way to boost productivity. Here are 5 aliases to put in your &lt;code&gt;~/.bashrc&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;~/.zshrc&lt;/code&gt; to keep them permanently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# ls: adding colors, verbose listing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# and humanize the file sizes:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;ls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;ls --color -l -h&quot;&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# grep: color and show the line&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# number for each match:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;grep&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;grep -n --color&quot;&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# mkdir: create parent directories:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;mkdir&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;mkdir -pv&quot;&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# ping: stop after 5 pings:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;ping&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;ping -c 5&quot;&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# curl: only display HTTP header:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;HEAD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;curl -I&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;# this create a new HEAD command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

</description>
